node.text: What's up guys. Matt Rees here. Co-founder of Ruroc. I wanted to put a message out to tell you about an incredible new mission of ours. @Enginehawk. Since we launched Atlas, we've found it hard to find motorcycle clothing that matches the level of design and performance of our helmets. We found that the gear we were forced to use was old school. It lacked great design, fit poorly, and the armor made it downright uncomfortable. And so we built a team. We recruited world class designers, and experts in engineering from the motorcycle industry. The result? motorcycle gear that looks better, fits better, and protects better. On April 27th, Enginehawk launches its first range of INSANE products. Follow the page for our new product releases over the next month and enjoy all the epic sh*t we've got to show you in the run up to the launch! #Ruroc #Enginehawk

To keep up with demand for Ruroc helmets, we’ve ditched the supply chains that big brands use and built our own factory. Every helmet that comes out of our new state of the art facility will be made faster, stronger and better quality than ever before, while ensuring the best working conditions for our staff.

The Ruroc factory is the next step in our mission to become the best helmet brand in the world. 💪

node.text:
BRAVE THE ELEMENTS

Every ATLAS 3.0 shell size has its own bespoke seal geometry, protecting you from all the elements. It’s the result of months of testing, revision and improvement to get the perfect fit. 

With the all new visor seal, air that would otherwise be trapped under the visor, is pulled out through the vent channel in the seal. This means you can open your chin vent, knowing that air will vent on either side of the helmet, aiding the de-misting process.

When riding through rain, the dynamic fluid path is outside of the path of the ventilation channel, guaranteeing that no water makes it into your helmet when riding. If you are waiting at the lights, the static fluid path also sits outside of the path of the ventilation channel, preventing water from entering the helmet.

Our Engineering team went through 8 different versions of the seal geometry before landing on the correct one. What does all this mean? Come rain or shine, ATLAS 3.0 keeps you cool, dry and protected from the elements. 💪

node.text:
TESTED FOR YEARS IN A SINGLE DAY.

How do you test years of opens and closes on an ATLAS 3.0 visor in just a single day? Build a custom machine, that’s how. We constructed a bespoke device to perform accelerated lifetime testing on multiple ATLAS 3.0 visor and mechanism designs. Our brief was clear. The visor had to perform just as well after three lifetimes of actuations, as it did on the first. 

We tested the open/close mechanism relentlessly, until we found the perfect combination of visor and mechanism that performed without fault. Then we tested it another 50 times, just to be sure. Building a helmet that performs flawlessly every time you reach for it is what we strive towards. When developing the Atlas 3.0 we undertook months of rigorous testing, improvements and refinements to create a helmet that is durable, safe and ready for anything. 💪

TESTED FOR YEARS IN A SINGLE DAY.

How do you test years of opens and closes on an ATLAS 3.0 visor in just a single day? Build a custom machine, that’s how. We constructed a bespoke device to perform accelerated lifetime testing on multiple ATLAS 3.0 visor and mechanism designs. Our brief was clear. The visor had to perform just as well after three lifetimes of actuations, as it did on the first. 

We tested the open/close mechanism relentlessly, until we found the perfect combination of visor and mechanism that performed without fault. Then we tested it another 50 times, just to be sure. Building a helmet that performs flawlessly every time you reach for it is what we strive towards. When developing the Atlas 3.0 we undertook months of rigorous testing, improvements and refinements to create a helmet that is durable, safe and ready for anything. 💪

VISION. REINFORCED.

Made from ballistic-grade polycarbonate, the Atlas 3.0 coverless visor has been designed to take a beating, so you don't have to. 💪 Backed by our next level design and engineering advances, our visors provide superior protection when you need it most. 

The shatterproof design of our polycarbonate means that impact from debris and stone chips will easily deflect, allowing you to maintain focus on the road. It also means that the visor can bend and contort to extremes angles, without a critical failure. 

Shipping with anti-scratch coating and Pinlock® compatibility as standard, the coverless visor system protects you from the worst roads, leaving you to enjoy the best ones.

VISION. REINFORCED.

Made from ballistic-grade polycarbonate, the Atlas 3.0 coverless visor has been designed to take a beating, so you don't have to. 💪 Backed by our next level design and engineering advances, our visors provide superior protection when you need it most. 

The shatterproof design of our polycarbonate means that impact from debris and stone chips will easily deflect, allowing you to maintain focus on the road. It also means that the visor can bend and contort to extremes angles, without a critical failure. 

Shipping with anti-scratch coating and Pinlock® compatibility as standard, the coverless visor system protects you from the worst roads, leaving you to enjoy the best ones.
